30/08/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- A police officer was shot and killed in the northern region of Shkodra early on Sunday (August 29th), prompting authorities to offer a 30,000-euro reward for information.
Kole Ndreshaj, 41, lived in Shkodra and worked as a traffic officer.
He was on his motorcycle when he was stopped by a car and shot from close range.
(Balkan Web, News 24, Top Channel, Ora News, Shekulli, Telegrafi - 29/08/10)
